<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="679" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/522</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-03T18:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s May 29, 3 p.m., June 19, 3 p.m., August 1, 6 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d679fn1">Telegram of Aug. 1 not printed.</note>
                                your June 3, 9 p.m. Cable Department full report of present status
                                of negotiations for lease from Peru of ex-German ships.</p>
                            <p>You are cautioned against saying anything to Peruvian Government
                                regarding guarantee which the United States Government is prepared
                                to make to Peru, against possible consequences which may come from
                                use of German ships. When it becomes necessary again to discuss this
                                guarantee the Department desires to make it a financial one and
                                include it in the actual contract for the ships as was done in the
                                lease for the ex-German ships in Uruguay.</p>
                            <p>Before undertaking patrol duty in Peruvian harbors, Navy Department
                                desires specific assurance that arrangement is approved by Peruvian
                                Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>